    "syns": [
      {
        "pl": "synonyms",
        "pt": [
          [
            "text",
            "{sc}feeling{/sc} {sc}emotion{/sc} {sc}affection{/sc} {sc}sentiment{/sc} {sc}passion{/sc} mean a subjective response to a person, thing, or situation. {sc}feeling{/sc} denotes any partly mental, partly physical response marked by pleasure, pain, attraction, or repulsion; it may suggest the mere existence of a response but imply nothing about the nature or intensity of it. "
          ],
          [
            "vis",
            [
              {
                "t": "the {it}feelings{/it} that once moved me are gone"
              }
            ]
          ],
          [
            "text",
            " {sc}emotion{/sc} carries a strong implication of excitement or agitation but, like {sc}feeling{/sc}, encompasses both positive and negative responses. "
          ],
          [
            "vis",
            [
              {
                "t": "the drama portrays the {it}emotions{/it} of adolescence"
              }
            ]
          ],
          [
            "text",
            " {sc}affection{/sc} applies to feelings that are also inclinations or likings. "
          ],
          [
            "vis",
            [
              {
                "t": "a memoir of childhood filled with {it}affection{/it} for her family"
              }
            ]
          ],
          [
            "text",
            " {sc}sentiment{/sc} often implies an emotion inspired by an idea. "
          ],
          [
            "vis",
            [
              {
                "t": "her feminist {it}sentiments{/it} are well known"
              }
            ]
          ],
          [
            "text",
            " {sc}passion{/sc} suggests a very powerful or controlling emotion. "
          ],
          [
            "vis",
            [
              {
                "t": "revenge became his ruling {it}passion{/it}"
              }
            ]
          ]
        ]
      }
    ],
